r Rogers, everything is of religious relevance: in addition to the social detail of the diary there is also a real and persuasive revelation of the spiritual meaning of Puritanism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPuritanszEnglandvDiaries. 0aPuritanszEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aModern History. 4aPhilosophy. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aCivil War.  aEnglish Puritanism.  aPuritan Perspective.  aPuritanism.  aReligious Relevance.  aSamuel Rogers.1 aShipps, Kenneth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWebster, Tom, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787441200?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787441200423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787441200/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles